<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-06T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-06T05:00:00-05:00" n="84" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9411/60: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-06T19:00:00+09:00">December 6,
                                1939—7 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received December 6—9:09 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>663. Department’s 385, December 5, 2 p.m. The Foreign Office today confirmed
                        the accuracy of the statement attributed to Suma but emphasized that the
                        statement presented only an objective fact and that no inference going
                        beyond the text would be warranted.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>